1 Section 1. (Deleted by amendment.)
2 Sec. 1.5. Chapter 450B of NRS is hereby amended by adding
3 thereto a new section to read as follows:
4 1. The board may, in consultation with persons who own or
5 operate an ambulance and fire-fighting agencies, adopt
6 regulations requiring that an applicant for certification as an
7 emergency medical technician, advanced emergency medical
8 technician or paramedic must have completed training concerning
9 interacting with elderly persons and persons who are cognitively
10 impaired. Any such regulations must require the training to
11 include, without limitation, instruction concerning:
12 (a) Recognizing and effectively interacting with elderly
13 persons in relevant settings;
14 (b) Identifying signs of cognitive impairment in a person and
15 using appropriate communication and de-escalation strategies in
16 interacting with such a person; and
17 (c) Providing person-centered care tailored to elderly persons
18 and persons who are cognitively impaired.
19 2. Any regulations adopted pursuant to this section must:
20 (a) Allow an applicant for certification who is subject to the
21 regulations to have completed the training described in subsection
22 1 as part of a program of training completed pursuant to NRS
23 450B.1905, 450B.191 or 450B.195; and
24 (b) Require the training described in subsection 1 to be
25 delivered by or developed by or in collaboration with a nationally
26 accredited or certified program with expertise in care for elderly
27 persons and persons who are cognitively impaired.
28 3. The board may not require a person who has completed
29 any training required by this section as part of the program of
30 training he or she completed pursuant to NRS 450B.1905,
31 450B.191 or 450B.195 to complete separate training.
